1. Download gslib and untar it at the level of the mfem folder.
   wget https://github.com/gslib/gslib/archive/v1.0.3.tar.gz
   tar -zxvf v1.0.3.tar.gz
   Now gslib should be located at the level of the MFEM folder

2. Build gslib in serial or parallel based on MFEM build:
   make clean;make CC=gcc MPI=0
   or
   make clean;make CC=mpicc MPI=1

3. Create a file mfem/config/user.mk, and add the line
   MFEM_USE_GSLIB = YES

4. Build mfem in serial or parallel, based on step 2.

5. Build the gslib findpts example in examples/gslib.
   make exp
   or 
   make exs
